  "prompt": "What is Fiverr, and how do they make money?",
  "response": "Fiverr is an online marketplace that connects freelancers with businesses and individuals looking for various services. The platform was founded in 2010 and has since grown to offer a wide range of services, from graphic design and writing to programming and marketing.\n\nFiverr makes money primarily through transaction fees. When a buyer purchases a service (known as a \"gig\") from a freelancer, Fiverr takes a percentage of the total transaction amount as a service fee. The standard fee is 20% of the total order amount, including the base price of the gig and any additional services or extras the buyer purchases.\n\nIn addition to transaction fees, Fiverr also offers a premium subscription service called Fiverr Pro, which provides buyers with access to vetted, high-quality freelancers and additional features like priority customer support. Fiverr Pro subscribers pay a monthly fee for this service, which contributes to the company's revenue.\n\nFiverr also generates income through its Fiverr Learn platform, which offers online courses and resources to help freelancers improve their skills and grow their businesses. Learners pay for access to these courses, providing another revenue stream for the company.\n\nOverall, Fiverr's business model is based on facilitating connections between freelancers and buyers while earning revenue through transaction fees, subscription services, and educational offerings.",
